Steve Wilson, CFA. Steve
Wilson founded Lapides Asset Management and serves as the firm's Chief
Investment Officer and as an Analyst/Manager. Steve has more
than 30 years experience conducting hands-on, proprietary
research, and managing portfolios of smaller cap securities. top 
Prior
to forming Lapides in June, 2005, Steve was an Analyst/Manager at Reich
& Tang since 1986. Additionally, he served for seven years as Chief
Investment Officer of the Capital Management Group at Reich & Tang.
Before joining Reich & Tang, Steve was President of Home Capital
Services, the investment management subsidiary of the Home Insurance
Company. 
Steve
has a BS from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania and
an MBA from New York University. He became a Chartered Financial
Analyst in 1984 and is a member of the New York Society of Security
Analysts. top Huck Fish.
Huck joined in October 2012 as a Research Assistant working in a
support role as part of our equity research group. Huck graduated from
Lafayette College in 2008 with a BS in Biology and has passed all three
levels of the CFA as of August 2012. topAndrey Seryy. Andrey joined Lapides Asset
Management LLC in August 2013 as an intern. He currently serves as a Research
Assistant supporting our equity research group. Before joining LAM he interned
at UBS Financial Services Inc. Andrey received a BS degree from Wayne State
University. top
Pushkar Bharambe.  Pushkar joined Lapides
Asset Management LLC as an intern in August 2015. He is currently working as a
Research Assistant as a part of our Equity Research group.  Pushkar
received his Masters in Financial Engineering from New York University and
holds a B.Engg in Electronics and Telecommunications from Pune University, India. top
Mary Hopkins. Mary
has been in market research for more than 25 years, including 17 years
at Guideline (now ORC Guideline and formerly FIND/SVP) in multiple
roles. For the past several years, she has worked independently analyst
researching and writing on a number of industries. 
Mary
has a Bachelor of Arts from the University of Pennsylvania. She has
taught market research classes at Columbia University and the Fashion
Institute of Technology (FIT) in New York City. top 
Jim Betz. Jim
joined Lapides Asset Management as its Chief Operating Officer in July,
2006, bringing more than 25 years of financial services industry
experience. Jim heads our operations, including finance, compliance and
administration. Jim came to Lapides from Nomura Securities
International, where he was Director of Financial and Regulatory
Reporting. 
Jim
founded CFO B/D Compliance, a consulting company to provide regulatory,
financial, and operational support to firms in the financial services
industry. Prior to starting his consultancy, he was Director of
Operations for the Safra Family Office, Safra National Bank and Safra
Securities Corp. Jim has also held senior financial/administrative
positions at a number of other firms, including Banorte Securities
International (Chief Financial Officer), Valores Finamex International,
Inc. (Chief Financial Officer), Serfin Securities, Inc. (Treasurer
& Controller), and Reich & Tang (Controller). 
Jim received a BS degree from St. Francis College and an MBA in Finance from Adelphi University. top Antoinette Francis. Antoinette
joined the firm in 2005 and serves as Vice President of Administration
/ Client Relations. Prior to that, she worked at Reich & Tang as
Administrative Assistant to Steve Wilson. She held various roles in
advertising and publishing before joining Reich & Tang in 2000.
Antoinette holds a BS degree from Long Island University - CW Post,
where she graduated Summa Cum Laude. top 
