performance is not indicative of future results.  Product performance is
calculated on an average annual total return basis, which includes income,
realized and unrealized gains and losses and reflects the deduction of
brokerage commissions and direct execution costs. Performance results for
periods prior to June 2005 represent the managing member’s record at a prior
firm. 
Unless
specifically footnoted, performance results reflect the deduction of investment
advisory fees, as well as, for limited partnerships, allowable expenses. A
client's return will be reduced by those fees and by any other management
expenses incurred by the account. For a description of Lapides’ fee structure,
please see Part II of our firm’s SEC Form ADV.
Each index is an unmanaged market weighted index that excludes fees,
commissions or other investment expenses.



