Lapides Asset Management Has Decreased Quanex Building Products (NX) Stake, Susquehanna International Group Llp Has Upped By $2.27 Million Its Advanced Energy Inds (AEIS) Position


					
						July 21, 2017 - By Winifred Garcia

Susquehanna International Group Llp increased Advanced Energy Inds (AEIS) stake by 158.21% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Susquehanna International Group Llp acquired 42,084 shares as Advanced Energy Inds (AEIS)’s stock rose 23.75%. The Susquehanna International Group Llp holds 68,684 shares with $3.76 million value, up from 26,600 last quarter. Advanced Energy Inds now has $2.99 billion valuation. The stock declined 0.35% or $0.26 reaching $75.5 on the news. About 136,485 shares traded. Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS) has risen 125.79% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 109.09% the S&P500.
Lapides Asset Management Llc decreased Quanex Building Products Corp (NX) stake by 25.92% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Lapides Asset Management Llc sold 24,000 shares as Quanex Building Products Corp (NX)’s stock rose 2.34%. The Lapides Asset Management Llc holds 68,600 shares with $1.39M value, down from 92,600 last quarter. Quanex Building Products Corp now has $738.84M valuation. The stock rose 0.94% or $0.2 reaching $21.4. About 26,881 shares traded. Quanex Building Products Corporation (NYSE:NX) has risen 12.06% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 4.64% the S&P500.






Among 5 analysts covering Quanex Building Products (NYSE:NX), 3 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 60% are positive. Quanex Building Products had 13 analyst reports since August 22, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The firm has “Outperform” rating by Wedbush given on Wednesday, March 8. Wedbush reinitiated it with “Outperform” rating and $25 target in Wednesday, July 19 report. The rating was maintained by Imperial Capital with “Outperform” on Tuesday, January 5. The firm has “Hold” rating given on Monday, August 31 by Wedbush. The company was initiated on Friday, September 25 by Sidoti. The rating was upgraded by KeyBanc Capital Markets on Friday, June 10 to “Overweight”. The rating was downgraded by TheStreet on Saturday, August 22 to “Buy”. The stock of Quanex Building Products Corporation (NYSE:NX) has “Sector Weight” rating given on Tuesday, October 18 by KeyBanc Capital Markets. Zacks upgraded the stock to “Hold” rating in Tuesday, September 22 report. The stock of Quanex Building Products Corporation (NYSE:NX) earned “Outperform” rating by Wedbush on Monday, March 14.
Investors sentiment increased to 1.78 in 2016 Q4. Its up 0.44, from 1.34 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 9 investors sold NX shares while 28 reduced holdings. 18 funds opened positions while 48 raised stakes. 33.58 million shares or 2.59% more from 32.73 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. New York-based Tiaa Cref Inv Llc has invested 0% in Quanex Building Products Corporation (NYSE:NX). Swiss National Bank has 0% invested in Quanex Building Products Corporation (NYSE:NX) for 52,800 shares. Barclays Public Limited Company holds 0% of its portfolio in Quanex Building Products Corporation (NYSE:NX) for 11,946 shares. Mutual Of America Mngmt Ltd Co has 95,000 shares for 0.04% of their portfolio. Moreover, Credit Suisse Ag has 0% invested in Quanex Building Products Corporation (NYSE:NX). Praesidium Invest Management Llc owns 3.33M shares for 5.48% of their portfolio. Principal Fin Group holds 0.01% or 250,940 shares in its portfolio. Ls Investment Advisors accumulated 1,202 shares. 56,228 were accumulated by Falcon Point Capital Ltd Liability Corp. Arizona State Retirement holds 0.01% or 17,636 shares in its portfolio. Cooke And Bieler LP holds 0.84% or 2.08M shares in its portfolio. Susquehanna International Llp holds 47,789 shares. Hbk Invests Limited Partnership reported 28,381 shares. Prudential owns 58,226 shares. Fisher Asset Management Lc holds 64,464 shares or 0% of its portfolio.
Analysts await Quanex Building Products Corporation (NYSE:NX) to report earnings on September, 5. They expect $0.31 EPS, up 3.33% or $0.01 from last year’s $0.3 per share. NX’s profit will be $10.70M for 17.26 P/E if the $0.31 EPS becomes a reality. After $0.11 actual EPS reported by Quanex Building Products Corporation for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts 181.82% EPS growth. 
Lapides Asset Management Llc increased Tegna Inc stake by 39,300 shares to 334,900 valued at $7.16M in 2016Q4. It also upped Web Com Group Inc (NASDAQ:WWWW) stake by 29,400 shares and now owns 217,000 shares. Mattel Inc (NASDAQ:MAT) was raised too. 
Since April 3, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 7 insider sales for $6.85 million activity. Shares for $480,120 were sold by GRADY EDWARD C. $1.14M worth of Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS) was sold by WASSERMAN YUVAL. On Monday, June 12 Liguori Thomas sold $379,464 worth of Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS) or 5,000 shares. MCGIMPSEY THOMAS O sold $2.29 million worth of stock or 29,772 shares. $274,240 worth of Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS) was sold by ROHRS THOMAS M.
Among 7 analysts covering Advanced Energy Industries Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS), 2 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 5 Hold. Therefore 29% are positive. Advanced Energy Industries Inc. had 17 analyst reports since August 5, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The stock of Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS) earned “Buy” rating by Dougherty & Company on Thursday, July 28. The firm has “Buy” rating by Needham given on Wednesday, August 5. Needham maintained Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS) rating on Wednesday, February 1. Needham has “Buy” rating and $70 target. The rating was maintained by Dougherty & Company on Thursday, January 12 with “Buy”. The stock has “Strong-Buy” rating by Zacks on Thursday, August 6. The firm has “Neutral” rating given on Wednesday, October 12 by Citigroup. Raymond James downgraded the stock to “Outperform” rating in Tuesday, January 5 report. The company was maintained on Wednesday, February 1 by Dougherty & Company. Susquehanna downgraded the shares of AEIS in report on Tuesday, April 19 to “Neutral” rating. Needham downgraded Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS) on Monday, April 18 to “Hold” rating.
Investors sentiment increased to 1.52 in 2016 Q4. Its up 0.41, from 1.11 in 2016Q3. It increased, as 17 investors sold AEIS shares while 70 reduced holdings. 55 funds opened positions while 77 raised stakes. 36.94 million shares or 0.75% more from 36.66 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Mackenzie Fin Corporation has 111,981 shares for 0.04% of their portfolio. Mckinley Llc Delaware owns 42,741 shares. Pinebridge Invs LP has invested 0.03% of its portfolio in Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS). Prudential Finance Inc invested in 0.06% or 651,843 shares. The Massachusetts-based Fmr Ltd Liability has invested 0% in Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS). Northcoast Asset Management Ltd Liability holds 0.08% in Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS) or 13,819 shares. Farmers & Merchants Investments, a Nebraska-based fund reported 130 shares. Hillcrest Asset Mngmt Ltd Liability Corp has invested 1.5% in Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS). Chesley Taft & Ltd Liability Co owns 24,675 shares for 0.13% of their portfolio. Icon Advisers holds 24,997 shares. Pillar Pacific Cap Llc invested 0.1% in Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS). Bbva Compass Bancshares Inc invested 0.06% in Advanced Energy Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:AEIS). Comml Bank Of America Corp De, a North Carolina-based fund reported 1.55 million shares. Deutsche National Bank Ag invested in 346,775 shares or 0.02% of the stock. Aperio Grp Ltd has 10,378 shares.



